com.github.basking2.sdsai.dsds.node

Interface NodeStore<USERKEY,STOREKEY,VALUE>

  • Type Parameters:
    USERKEY - The user's key.
    STOREKEY - The key type used by the storage medium.
    VALUE - The values stored.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DirectoryNodeStore, IONodeStore, TransactionalNodeStore

    public interface NodeStore<USERKEY,STOREKEY,VALUE>

    The bridge code from Java objects to stored documents. Implementors of this interface will be doing much of what a DAO would do, and a little more. Specifically functions like convert(Object) and generateKey(Node, Object) are critical but not something a traditional DAO would exposing.

    All exceptions are NodeStoreExceptions which is itself a RuntimeException. Note that loadNode(Object) is unique in that it will throw a NodeStoreNodeNotFoundException (which is a type of NodeStoreException).

      • generateKey

        STOREKEY generateKey(Node<USERKEY,STOREKEY> node,
                     VALUE value)
        Generate a key to store a node or data element. This key must be unique.
        Parameters:
        node - This is provided to implementations for some context. If generateKey is being called for the purposes of storing a user key, this will be null.
        value - If a key is being generated for a user key value, it will be passed along. This is most useful when things like a PagedList are adding a value, but the List API does not provide a way to specify a key.
        Throws:
        NodeStoreException

      • convert

        STOREKEY convert(USERKEY key)
        Convert user keys to store keys. This method, given a user's key, must always produce the same store key.
        Throws:
        NodeStoreException - if any error occurs.
